g.text: Black dots show coefficient estimates from one run of a stepwise (AIC-based) model fitting. Red squares show correct values.
Variables' coefficients are most often either zero (ie dropped by the stepwise procedure), or too large.
Also, real explanatory variables are often dropped. Fake ones are often included.
Stepwise regression returns coefficient estimates biased away from zero
Simulated data with a model that explains about 27% of variation in response variable, with mild multicollinearity, by https://freerangestats.info
